{"word":"Συμεών","slug":"Συμεών","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Συμεών, ὁ</el></b> [Semitic name] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ indecl.\">indecl.</a> <b>Symeon, Simeon<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> son of Jacob and ancestor of tribe bearing his name <b><a href='B:730 7:7'>Rv 7:7</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ancestor of Jesus <b><a href='B:490 3:30'>Lk 3:30</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>3.</pp></b> one who welcomed the infant Jesus <b><a href='B:490 2:25'>Lk 2:25</a>, <a href='B:490 2:34'>34</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>4.</pp></b> surnamed Niger <b><a href='B:510 13:1'>Ac 13:1</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>5.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ a.k.a.\">a.k.a.</a> the apostle Peter <b><a href='B:510 15:14'>Ac 15:14</a>; <a href='B:680 1:1'>2 Pt 1:1</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:σύμβουλος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:συμμαθητής\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}